Q.1] Write a python program to accept a string, find all words that do not contain vowels.

s = input("Enter a string: ")
words = s.split()
for w in words:
    if not any(v in w.lower() for v in "aeiou"):
        print(w)



Q.2] Write a python program to create a list of prime numbers between m and n using List comprehension. (Accept the value of m and n from user, m should be less than n)

m = int(input("Enter m: "))
n = int(input("Enter n: "))
if m >= n:
    print("m should be less than n")
else:
    primes = [x for x in range(m, n+1)
              if x > 1 and all(x % i != 0 for i in range(2, int(x**0.5)+1))]
    print("Prime numbers:", primes)
